caption: The owner was super nice and rhe food is good. Take out due to restrictions.
Great food as always but the name is now Similar Thai - Sushi

This is my favorite Thai restaurant in IL!  They have the most amazing noodle soups.  The Summer Noodles & Rice is so flavorful.  The broth is a little sour, salty, sweet, and spicy.   It's just perfect.  You can also choose the noodle you want in each of the broth.  I also love the beef noodle soup.  All the soups are totally unique and delicious.  This restaurant is probably closest to what you would get in Thailand.
New moto in life, Always check the box for crispy noodles! Absolutely delish pad thai!!
Price isn't too bad, but unfortunately that's all I can really say about the food as well.
The workers are the friendliest and their food is excellent.
The food was very delicious.
Summer never fails to deliver. The food is always fresh, hot, and delicious. Can’t recommend them enough; my personal fave is the Basil Fried Rice!
Great food, friendly staff, and great prices.
Great
Excellent food and fast service

First time visit, very nice place. The menu has plenty of options. The meal was very tasty, I would say it's a hidden gem. Try this place instead of Argyle street, you will not be disappointed. Try the soups as well. Best wishes to the staff!
Delicious. Gyoza was great
Everything is fine, but be aware from hot and spicy 🥵
Super nice staff and the food was really good

Food was clean and fresh! I didn't feel disgusting after eating their house fried rice, orange chicken, and spring rolls. I loved the cucumber salad they sent along. Not your typical chinese spot and I enjoyed every bite of it. Thanks!

Cozy place and the food is cooked well and very tasty. I ordered Pad Thai and my friend got orange chicken. We're happy with our meal. Highly recommended. There are a lot of street parking and the Granville CTA Redline is next door.
Had a really good meal! The noodles were delicious and the lunch specials are at a good price point. Service is quick!
Very good Thai food, lovely atmosphere
Food was good and they kept their kitchen open late to welcome more guests!
Space is pleasant, nicely decorated with photographs. Servers are attentive.  Many menu choices and good quality.
Good food, good price, good people. Restaurant was clean.
I have not had better tom ka soup. Their pad thai is on point and so are their curries.

Food was very good! This is a solid BYOB restaurant. Only downside is that the customer service is slow, but I do understand that this place does a lot of takeout business. As long as you aren't in any rush, I recommend this place for some delicious Asian cuisine.

This place is super quaint and clean. They got the cutest little decor without over doing it. Dimly lit with candles. And the fact that its right next to the granville redline spot adds a special touch. The place vibrates a little when the train passes by lol which i love. The people who work there are so nice and accommodating. They always make me feel welcomed. Now the food! The food is stellar! I love their spicy mango shrimp. So delicious and so filling. All in all this place is a sweet gem in edgewater! 😋
The summer tempura is amazing as are all the dishes we have had there.
Pretty decent food quality for the price. The soup was delicious.
Always consistent quality. Go with the Thai fried rice.
Friendly people! Great decor! Tasty food! Great prices! A super win all around!
Good Chicken Pad Thai served in a moderately priced, small, upscale decorated but casual restaurant.

This place has great duck dishes!  All plates are artfully prepared and presented.  Quite tasty and varied mix of Asian dishes.  I often get the Shiitake Egg Foo Yung and really  like it.  A modern feel with clean lines.  Right next to the Red Line Granville L stop.
Never disappoints! Food and service excellent.
One of my go to places!!

Curry fried rice with pineapple, garlic noodles with tofu and Pad Thai are all very tasty. The chicken satay and gyoza both cooked to perfection. Counter staff very nice. It's right by the Granville El stop. Order on Berwyn and it'll be ready by time you get there.
Delicious Thal food.  Just under the Red Line Granville stop.
The food was good, but small portion of rice. Most places that serve this type of food serve a lot of rice.
My best friend almost died eating here. Got food poisoning and was sick for three days with explosive diarriah.  Eat If you dare.
Nice place n people, but their food is too greasy.

Ordered chive dumplings & house fried rice from them. The dumplings were soggy & RAW on the inside, completely oily & inedible. I asked for the fried rice to be spicy (my mistake) it was overwhelming & I could barely taste the actual food. I returned the food & asked for a refund, they only refunded me on 1 of the items. Horrible experience, will never order from them again👎🏽🚮😷
Delicious apps. And the noodles are almost better cold, a few to 25 hours later

Great local Thai place. Great versions of Thai classics and new creations all rock. Women who work there are all very nice and Sue the owner makes you feel very welcome. Love the pork skewers with sticky rice and dynamite scallop. Right under Granville el stop. Never let down eating here ever.
Still AMAZING! Kept it simple with chicken and shrimp stir fried hand Summer Noodles & Rice and I'll tell you it's STILL worth the trip from the Bronx!
Pad Thai - EXCELLENT I ordered the lunch special and it was delicious must try!
Excellent food, nice relaxed vibe!
Good food! Great place . Chicken lo mein with the Thai iced tea>>>>
Authentic Thai food. I like Thai iced tea and mango sticky rice a lot.
Good food, friendly staff and inexpensive prices..what more could you ask for?

While recovering from a pretty bad stomach ache, I was looking for places near me that had a nice chicken soup. Luckily, Summer Noodles was there! I went there and was greeted by a very comfortable and cozy atmosphere, and very nice employees. The chicken soup was hearty and flavorful, without being too strong for my then-weak stomach. I will definitely tell friends about the place, and try more dishes later!

We recently dined here for the first time, with friends who had previously dined at the restaurant. We also had  two visiting Monks with our party. The young lady who assisted us, was so helpful and patient. She went above and beyond to help accommodate our honored guests. Even taking pictures during the blessing. We will definitely be back!
I like their pork buns.
Delicious mango smoothie with tapioca and the crab rangoons were the best ive had. Great restaurant!
Fantastic food Great Service I always feel at-home
Excellent food. Indian's would love this place.
Nice
I ♡ summers! Their lunch special is a STEAL! and absolutely love their food presentation. My compliments to the chef.
Loved the lunch special. Reasonably priced and large portions
Love this spot! I would suggest dining in not just because they have a really cute atmosphere, but also because their portion size shrinks considerably if you do take-out or delivery!
Thus was a pleasant surprise. Excellent food at reasonable prices.
Delicious authentic thai food at reasonable prices
Nice and calm place. Great Thai food
Good service and tasty food, the lunch deals are my favorite. This place also is BYOB and has a discount for Loyola students if you’re paying cash.
Omg.   Eat here!   Sooooo good!   Soooo fast!   Sooooo worth the price!
Okay
Good, genuine pan-Asian food, good service, comfortably elegant
Great food and the lunch special (before 3pm, 7 days a week) cannot be beat. Soup, appetizer, and entree for $8.95.

Intimate, classy space and I had my order within 10 minutes. Forgot to take a pic of my dish (hungry!) but it was great -- Hot Popeye with spinach noodles! The "balls of noodles" lamps above the barare hand-crafted by the owner Sue's nephew. Named Summer -- respite in a cold climate for sure.
A nice local spot to get some Thai inspired food. A little pricier than my go to, but still good.
A good thai restaurant
Only had the Ginger wonton. Love it!
Great byob spot
Always clean, always great food, always awesome service.  Absolutely a favorite place.
Nice and quaint with tasty food. The owner and staff are friendly.

Service was horrible, came in to get some smoothies and they ignored me for a good 5 minutes, once they finally took my order with some attitude from the waitress I waited 30 minutes just to get 2 mango smoothies!!! This is outrageous, would not recommend to anyone they were rude and impolite towards me. If I could rate it 0 stars I would.
The price is a little high but the presentation is excellent.
Spicy basil chicken ftw!
Super suprised! Clean, friendly and tasty food.
Great food and prices. The staff is polite, and the atmosphere feels classy but not stuffy.
SUMMER IS AWESOME  never had a bad experience in the 7 years I have been eating here. Thanks for being amazing y’all.
The food here is amazing and eating in is cozy and comfortable. My favorite dish is their Yellow Curry, so yummy every time!
Their special are great and only $10-$15.
Lots of vegetarian options. Good food, good price.
Food is visually appealing and delicious.

Food is alright, proved are reasonable but they have these sneaky policies to charge you higher if you order online. There is no sign in the restaurant or anything online that says they charge you .50 cents extra for using your card. There is always an issue with them. Service is horrible. I'd go back only if I was desperate.
I love this place. Delicious, affordable Thai food. I generally stick to their noodle dishes and am not quite as big of a fan of their other entrees. The noodles are great!
My favorite Thai place! They are always polite.
The best spinach noodles , everything is so  jummy and the music makes yo feel so relaxed. I loved it
Great food, and we got it quickly! The restaurant is nice, with a cozy modern feel and some cool color-changing lights. The Thai iced tea tasted as good as it looked, and all our food was amazing!
I recommend the shrimp shumai. The spicy BBQ pork was correctly spicy but the pork was not so tender
The atmosphere and good was great! The ginger beef is great as is the crab rangoon and chicken egg rolls. The dumplings are incredible, as well! Definitely stop here if you love Asian food!

Really good food, price is just a little high for the portion size, but I left feeling full, and the food is really quite good. Staff is friendly, but not the most attentive. The smoothies are good, too.
Great food
Great food great service great people excellent prices we come often who could ask for anything more
This place it's awesome, berry welcoming and Cosy. I have been coming to this place since 2010 and it is still my number one choice. FYI the spicy mango shrimp is to die for!
I had the pad Thai. It was really good. The gyoza was good too. Cool environment inside. The smoothie was a little watery
lovedd everything here
The service is horrible, if you have a coupon or Groupon, the waitress acts like it's free food and expects you to be happy you get served.

This place is racist and rude! I mentioned I have a Groupon right after I ordered my food for take out. The waitress said they don't allow take out for a Groupon. I was fine with that, and agreed to dine in with my boyfriend. She kept mentioning multiple times that we can't take leftovers to go with a Groupon. That was weird rule, but we were not going to take leftovers anyway. The food was mediocre and bland. When she brought the check, we showed our Groupon, she took the number, and gave the receipt for the $3 that went over the $30 Groupon. She said tip was not included in that, like we don't know. We ignored, and let her charge. She puts in a tip by herself and charged my card! That was ridiculous! For the kind of service she offered, I was not going to tip her 25%. The last time I was there, I was not charged a tip, I tipped as I desired. This place is not even close to the rear end of a high-end place that charge a standard tip. The customer should decide how much they want to tip! This is unacceptable for a place like this!
The Yellow curry with Tofu is phenomenal
My favorite take out Thai place. Also have great Thai iced tea and lunch specials

I love this place!  The ambience is romantic and chic while the prices are super affordable!!!  Why pay $9.00 for a takeout dish when you can dine in and have it at the same price but for higher quality entrees and an atmosphere that can't be matched at that price.
You must try basil duck with tomzab soup!!!!
Delicious and fresh good. Place very clean and pleasant. We will come back
Summer rolls presented in a unique way. Very fresh and tasty. Pad Thai was excellent. Server very pleasant and efficient.
Best Chicken  Pad Thai in the city of Chicago!  Warm and cozy, nice owner and wait staff
Good setting. Amazing food.
Staff was nice and food was great. Prices look like they've recently gone up.
Great food, fast service, and a wonderful environment. Quiet and relaxed.
This is my actual favorite restaurant in Chicago. Great service, great food,  cozy modern atmosphere, and byob!
The Pad Thai was amazing! I would definitely go back again!
Great lunch specials and dishes all around. I can make a meal out of all the starters!
The green and red curry is the best in the neighborhood. Very clean and the service is great
Nice noodles with tofu, a good option for vegetarians, and I love their shakes with tapioca balls

Summer Noodle is probably one of, if not, my favorite place for Thai food. I've dined in, picked up and ordered for delivery. The staff is always very nice and accommodating when I dine in or call to place an order. They deliver faster than the expected time given, which I absoluetly love! Especially on the days that I'm craving their food lol. The delivery guy is awesome! The food is always really fresh and hot! If you haven't tried out this restaurant, please do! It's a must!
The food is almost always yummy.  The service is adequate, but every OTHER time there's some sort of issue (and we are not picky).  So, we keep going back, but we go less and less.
They have great food 👌🏼 hands down , I usually go there but I ordered delivery and the person who I spoke to was rude
I ordered a sweet and sour chicken. There was barely any chicken and it was pretty tough. I wasted my time.
The Rama Chicken is pretty nice. Great and flavorful peanut sauce. I did a pick up from this place and they were quick in getting my food ready.
I am addicted to their green tea bubble tea. Go in and get one and you won't be disappointed. Creamy and not too sweet :)
Great food at a reasonable price, with a nicely decorated dining space. Very accessible as it is right next to the Granville station doors.
Summer tempura is a delight for vegetarians here.. Prices are reasonable.. This is my go to place for Thai food
I was pleasantly surprised by my visit today. Food was very good for the price and the service was fast despite only having one server.
Tempora is very awesome. Their presentation of dish is very beautiful.
Delicious food! Great lunch special with large portion sizes, and don't forget to get a green tea smoothie- my favorite!
Server was rude the whole time. She told me they do not accept cards, when I've paid with cards before and saw the machine from where I was sitting.
The food is always consistent and very good.  The lunch special is also a great deal and gives plenty of food.  Great place to grab a quick bite or to have a nice dinner at!
Presentation and quality are always on point! Cute spot and delicious food!
This is my favorite Thai restaurant l. The food is always delicious and very reasonably priced. The service is great. The atmosphere is just perfect.  I highly recommend this place.

My boyfriend and I are regulars at Summer - we often take out an appetizer of crab rangoon and two Bangkok Chowfun dishes. Crab rangoon (Summer Cheese) is always on point, the fried wonton always thin and the cream cheese always hot and soft. Bangkok Chowfun (pad-see-ewn) is our favorite but I've tried many other dishes here like Cashew Duck, Pad Thai, Orange Chicken and more that I've enjoyed. I don't think the food is very authentic but they put their own twist to common dishes and make it work. The service is always good, I haven't seen many new faces since the three years I've been coming to Summer so I'm guessing management is good and they enjoy working here.

I was in the mood for orange chicken and walked over to the Granville Redline stop to see what I could find. I walked in and ordered for carry-out, no problem. The price for an order of orange chicken is $7.75, which sounded reasonable to me. I also ordered some crab rangoon. I waited about 10 minutes for my food and then left. When I got home and opened the carry-out bag, I noticed how small the portions were. I understand that the carry-out containers are probably smaller than the ones used when dining in, but I doubt that four (soggy) pieces of orange chicken suffice as an entree. The crab rangoon were very tasty, but there were only six tiny pieces for $5 and I didn't feel like the price equaled the amount of food I was given. Perhaps if the portions were bigger, I would've reviewed this place a bit higher.
Delicuous!  The lunch special is very good. I had crab ragoon, sweet cucumber salad and pad see wee for $7. They made me a rice and mango dessert in a butterfly shape. Really cute!
Not a bad place. It's a small little restaurant near the Granville Red-Line stop. The food is alright. I wasn't overly thrilled by my order or the service. Went a couple times and wasn't impressed.

This tiny little restaurant is one of my favorite places! Hands down best thai food in the area.  Everything they make is light and not greasy or drowning in sauce like other places do.  Awesome ambiance as well :)

Good, but not the best. A fun ambiance that leans towards the feminine side, the service was good, but not superb. My order was mediocre, but I still was okay with eating it. I wouldn't complain, but for the price and the location, I would head across the street to Thai Grill instead.

Summer is a very good thai restaurant. It has a nice ambiance rigth from when you walk in the door. Then once you sit down, you are given great service and good food. You don't have to wait to long for your meal and it is always delicious. Come and eat!!
Cheap and tasty. Not the most authentic but it doesn't even matter because the veggies are fresh and delicious!
The food here is great and the price is very reasonable for the amount of food you get. The ambiance is very nice to sit down and the staff is very friendly.
Summer is the most chill and cute little place. There is hardly ever a wait and their food is so amazing. I highly reccommend the crab rangoon and any dish with chicken!
Horrible service and strong mold smell in dining room.
I love the veggie eggrolls and their forks.
